article_title: Joe Biden's Mission: Unite Japan, South Korea
article_text:
China's muscle-flexing over its new air-defense identification zone has made a key U.S. goal even more urgent: pushing America's two most important allies in Asia—Japan and South Korea—closer together.

Yet at the end of a week of diplomacy in a tense North Asia, Vice President Joe Biden could report no progress on a more united front to counter Beijing's growing assertiveness.
